// news-feed.arch — golden fixture (DGC-31)
//
// A deeper "design a news feed" system-design sketch than url-shortener.arch:
// a public edge (CDN + load balancer) fronting a VPC that holds two nested
// tiers — the stateless "Feed service" tier and the stateful "Data stores"
// tier — plus a Kafka topic shared by both for the fan-out write path.
//
// Fan-out-on-write flow (a user publishes a post):
//   Client -> CDN -> LB -> API Gateway -> Auth Service        (verify token)
//                                       -> Fanout Worker
//   Fanout Worker -> Postgres                                 (persist post)
//                 -> Redis Cache                               (write feed cache)
//                 -> Kafka Queue                                (enqueue fanout job)
//   Kafka Queue -> Notification Service                       (consume, push to followers)
//   API Gateway -> Search Index                                (index post for search)
//               -> Object Storage                              (upload attached media)

direction right

Client [icon: monitor]
CDN [icon: cloud, color: purple]
LB [icon: network, color: blue]

VPC {
  Feed service {
    API Gateway [icon: server, color: orange]
    Auth Service [icon: lock, color: gray]
    Fanout Worker [icon: cpu, color: yellow]
    Notification Service [icon: bell, color: pink]
  }

  Data stores {
    Redis Cache [icon: redis, color: red]
    Postgres [icon: postgresql, color: blue]
    Object Storage [icon: hard-drive, color: gray]
    Search Index [icon: elasticsearch, color: teal]
  }

  Kafka Queue [icon: apachekafka, color: black]
}

Client > CDN
CDN > LB
LB > API Gateway: HTTPS request

API Gateway > Auth Service: verify token
API Gateway > Fanout Worker: publish post
API Gateway > Search Index: index post
API Gateway > Object Storage: upload media

Fanout Worker > Postgres: persist post
Fanout Worker > Redis Cache: write feed cache
Fanout Worker > Kafka Queue: enqueue fanout job

Kafka Queue > Notification Service: consume fanout job

